performed_via_github_app.name: Codecov
performed_via_github_app.description:
Codecov provides highly integrated tools to group, merge, archive and compare coverage reports. Whether your team is comparing changes in a pull request or reviewing a single commit, Codecov will improve the code review workflow and quality.

## Code coverage done right.Â®

1. Upload coverage reports from your CI builds.
2. Codecov merges all builds and languages into one beautiful coherent report.
3. Get commit statuses, pull request comments and coverage overlay via our browser extension.

When Codecov merges your uploads it keeps track of the CI provider (inc. build details) and user specified context, e.g. `#unittest` ~ `#smoketest` or `#oldcode` ~ `#newcode`. You can track the `#unittest` coverage independently of other groups. [Learn more here](
http://docs.codecov.io/docs/flags)

Through **Codecov's Browser Extension** reports overlay directly in GitHub UI to assist in code review in [Chrome](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/codecov/gedikamndpbemklijjkncpnolildpbgo) or Firefox (https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/codecov/)

*Highly detailed* **pull request comments** and *customizable* **commit statuses** will improve your team's workflow and code coverage incrementally.

**File backed configuration** all through the `codecov.yml`. 

## FAQ
- Do you **merge multiple uploads** to the same commit? **Yes**
- Do you **support multiple languages** in the same project? **Yes**
- Can you **group coverage reports** by project and/or test type? **Yes**
- How does **pricing** work? Only paid users can view reports and post statuses/comments.

issue.title: Add a button for copying file path
issue.body:
### Problem Statement

Currently, to copy a file path from a trace error, I have to highlight the text with my mouse... then, as I'm using a good operating system, I can paste it with the middle mouse button. 

![error report](https://33fa1ur95-aho52jjqm.sentry.dev/static/4fce691c975e23b7d742f3b2a6b604be/237b5/codecov-sentry-integration.webp)

### Solution Brainstorm

The idea is to add a simple button on each line, so that when I click on it, the file path is copied.

```js
<button 
 onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText(this.getAttribute('data-file'));"
 data-file="..." data-line="123"
 class="sentry-copy-btn"
>copy</button>
```

And, if you install this **EXPERIMENTAL** [web extension](https://addons.mozilla.org/firefox/addon/openfileeditor/), I can easily replace the onclick with another one, so then when you click on the copy button, it open directly your favorite text editor with the file.

### Product Area

Issues

comment.body: Even if you don't have a full path. Just copy the file name then. The first thing I do every time I see an error is I want to open the code in my editor. Which means I'm manually copying whatever information you give me and then pasting it in my IDE to find it. I've been doing that for so long at this point, I can't be the only one.

issue.title: Add System.Text.Json support to AdaptiveCards .NET library
issue.body:
This PR implements System.Text.Json serialization and deserialization support for the AdaptiveCards .NET library, providing a modern alternative to the existing Newtonsoft.Json implementation.

## Overview

The AdaptiveCards library now supports both Newtonsoft.Json (existing) and System.Text.Json (new) for JSON operations, allowing developers to migrate to modern .NET JSON APIs while maintaining full backward compatibility.

## Key Features

### New API Methods
- `AdaptiveCard.ToJsonSystemText()` - Serialize using System.Text.Json
- `AdaptiveCard.FromJsonSystemText(json)` - Deserialize using System.Text.Json
- Existing Newtonsoft.Json methods (`ToJson()`, `FromJson()`) remain unchanged

### Clean JSON Output
Both serializers now produce similar, minimal JSON:

```json
{
  "type": "AdaptiveCard",
  "version": "1.0",
  "fallbackText": "This card requires a newer client",
  "body": [
    {
      "text": "Hello, World!",
      "color": "accent",
      "size": "large",
      "weight": "bolder",
      "type": "TextBlock"
    }
  ],
  "actions": [
    {
      "type": "Action.Submit",
      "id": "submitButton",
      "title": "Submit"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Usage Example

```csharp
// Create a card
var card = new AdaptiveCard("1.0");
card.Body.Add(new AdaptiveTextBlock("Hello, World!")
{
    Size = AdaptiveTextSize.Large,
    Weight = AdaptiveTextWeight.Bolder
});

// Serialize with System.Text.Json (new)
string json = card.ToJsonSystemText();

// Deserialize with System.Text.Json (new)
var result = AdaptiveCard.FromJsonSystemText(json);
var deserializedCard = result.Card;
```

## Technical Implementation

- **DTO Pattern**: Uses clean Data Transfer Objects for JSON representation
- **Polymorphic Support**: Handles different element and action types correctly
- **Minimal Changes**: Non-invasive addition that preserves all existing functionality
- **Comprehensive Testing**: Full test suite validates compatibility and functionality

## Currently Supported

âœ… **Core Elements**
- AdaptiveCard (all properties)
- AdaptiveTextBlock (complete formatting support)

âœ… **Actions**
- AdaptiveSubmitAction
- AdaptiveOpenUrlAction

âœ… **Features**
- Version handling and validation
- Card-level properties (fallbackText, speak, lang, etc.)
- Element properties (spacing, separator, visibility)
- Text formatting (size, weight, color, wrap)
- Clean JSON serialization/deserialization

## Benefits

1. **Modern .NET Support**: Ready for modern .NET applications using System.Text.Json
2. **Performance**: Potential performance improvements over Newtonsoft.Json
3. **Reduced Dependencies**: Less reliance on external JSON libraries
4. **Side-by-Side Migration**: Both APIs work together during gradual migration
5. **Backward Compatibility**: Existing code continues to work unchanged

## Future Enhancements

This implementation provides a solid foundation for expanding System.Text.Json support to additional element types (Image, Container, Input elements) and specialized converters as needed.

## Documentation

Complete usage documentation and examples are included in `docs/SystemTextJsonSupport.md`.

Fixes #9146.

borg 1.2.6

#### Operating system (distribution) and version.

macOS 13.5.1 (22G90)

#### Full borg commandline that lead to the problem (leave away excludes and passwords)

`borg info /Volumes/BACKUP2/borgbackup`

update: it can also happen with `borg create --stats` as the root cause is in the stats computation code.

## Describe the problem you're observing.

I am getting the output `Data integrity error: Archive authentication did not verify`. This is new (borg has been working fine) and it occured in all three repositories (local volume & ssh) at once.

#### Include any warning/errors/backtraces from the system logs

```
# borg info /Volumes/BACKUP2/borgbackup
Enter passphrase for key /Volumes/BACKUP2/borgbackup:
Repository ID: [redacted]
Location: /Volumes/BACKUP2/borgbackup
Encrypted: Yes (repokey BLAKE2b)
Cache: /Users/user/.cache/borg/[redacted]
Security dir: /Users/user/.config/borg/security/[redacted]
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                       Original size      Compressed size    Deduplicated size
Data integrity error: Archive authentication did not verify
 ```

comment.body:
From IRC:
```
12:21  jssfr$ hm, I'm late to *that* party, but I expect you'll see more of that now that Debian Trixie released with the CVE-2023-36811 fix.
12:22  jssfr$ is there any way I can sensibly run in an intermediate state?
12:22  jssfr$ I have dozens of clients backing up to the same server, and that server also does checking
12:22  jssfr$ the repositories are thus unencrypted
12:22  jssfr$ does that even affect me then?

13:42  sweatiest$ jssfr: Do you have a version <=1.2.5? Are you planning to upgrade to 1.4?

13:45  jssfr$ sweatiest, I have a dozen or so boxes, backing up to two different servers.
13:45  jssfr$ most are currently on bookworm (< 1.2.5), I'm starting ot upgrade to trixie (1.4.0)
13:46  jssfr$ I cannot do them all at the same time, not enough time for that.
13:46  jssfr$ I'll have to stretch the process over weeks/months

16:17  ThomasWaldmann$ jssfr: make sure you completely read the CVE notes in the borg changelog, i described everything in detail there.
16:21  ThomasWaldmann$ if the server runs borg check [--repair], i think you should keep the server on borg < 1.2.5 until you have upgraded all clients and 
                       all repos (procedure as described in the changelog).
16:32  ThomasWaldmann$ borg >= 1.2.5 always "authenticate" archives. if there is secret key material, this is a strong, cryptographic authentication. if 
                       there is no secret key (--encryption=none), it will do the same, but as there is no real secret, it will be rather weak.
```

issue.title: feat: index.js refactoring, real-time save settings, add settings snapshots, chat room renaming and bug fixes

labels.name: enhancement
labels.description: Modify behavior of existing feature or function

labels.name: pending for author
labels.description: PR is reviewed. Waiting for the author to address the review comments.

issue.body:
This pull request introduces a major refactoring of the codebase to a component-based architecture, along with new features and several bug fixes.

Key changes include:

**Features:**
- Implement real-time settings and snapshot management:
    - Settings now save on input change with debouncing for performance.
    - New settings snapshot feature to automatically save up to 10 previous versions.
    - Improved "Cancel" button in settings to revert unsaved changes with confirmation.
- Inline Chat Room Renaming: 
    - Implemented inline editing for chat room names 
    - Includes a confirm button for explicit save and hides non-essential UI elements during rename.

**Refactoring:**
- Decompose index.js into a component-based structure:
    - UI rendering logic extracted into `src/components/`.
    - New `src/ui.js` for component rendering orchestration.
    - Event handling moved to `src/handlers/`.
    - Utilities separated into `api.js`, `storage.js`, `utils.js`.
- Pass prompts explicitly to API calls and add transparent favicons.
- Refactored API calls to use an options object for improved clarity and maintainability.
- Improved error handling and code readability in storage and utility functions.
- Used handler mapping for `handleModalInput`.

**Bug Fixes:**
- Apply font scale on page load.
- Correct errors in random first talk feature.
- Prevent message input loss on new character addition.
- Correct backup and restore logic in storage:
    - `handleBackup` now sources data from live application state to prevent data loss.
    - `handleRestore` now correctly restores `chatRooms` and `userStickers` with fallback defaults.
- Fix issues identified during refactoring:
    - UI rendering on initial load.
    - Removed call to non-existent `addKeyboardListeners`.
- Fixed a critical bug where chat room name changes were not persisted due to incorrect state mutation.
- Resolved an issue where the inline editing UI for chat rooms would not appear correctly.
- Fixed a bug causing the chat room deletion modal to remain open after completion.
- Addressed issues with character edit/delete modals not appearing immediately, ensuring correct state change detection. 
    - Prevented settings modal from resetting/collapsing during auto-save by moving snapshot creation to an explicit save action. 
    - Fixed character deletion confirmation modal not closing.
- Added a 500ms debounce to settings inputs to prevent UI lag and excessive re-rendering.
- Corrected event handling for character edit and delete buttons in the sidebar.
- Changed `checkStorageSpace` warning limit (renamed to `getLocalStorageFallbackUsage`).
- Applied fixes based on PR review.
